  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAs raised by @q9f in https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/issues/5616, Lighthouse is triggering genesis too late. It's due to this line:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a50ade3ffcfdbab78c82f610d90920669ebe4ed9/beacon_node/genesis/src/eth1_genesis_service.rs#L226-L228\r\n\r\nI _think_ this is an artifact of an old spec that never got cleaned up, not sure though.\r\n\r\nRegardless, it should look more like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n.filter(|block | block.timestamp - block.timestamp % MIN_GENESIS_DELAY + 2 * MIN_GENESIS_DELAY >= spec.min_genesis_time)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because it _is_ possible for genesis to be triggered by a `eth1_block.timestamp` that is less than `MIN_GENESIS_TIME`.",
